  "description": "Erection of a two-storey roof extension incorporating a mansard style roof to 10 &amp; 12 Brett Road, to facilitate creation of 2 x 1 bed flats (Use Class C3)",
  "lapsed_date": "28/07/2022",
  "lpa_app_no": "2021/1823",
  "last_updated": "2025-03-20T12:50:47.895+00:00",
  "application_type": "All Other",
  "site_name": "10-12 Brett Road, Hackney, London, E8 1JP",
  "appeal_decision_date": null,
  "site_number": "10",
  "appeal_decision": null,
  "development_type": "Minor all other minor developments",
  "appeal_start_date": null,
  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: 1.2;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;The proposed two storey extension, by virtue of its height, location, detailed design and massing would dominate the host building and existing street scene representing an inappropriate form of development that would fail to respect the architectural integrity of the host building and would fail to integrate into the wider street scene, to the detriment of the visual amenity of the host building and the conservation area. As such the proposal is contrary to policies D4 (Delivering good design) and HC1(Heritage, Conservation and Growth) of the London Plan 2021 and policy LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character) and LP3(Designated Heritage Assets) of the Hackney Local Plan 2020.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to contribute towards the Carbon Offset Fund,&amp;nbsp; would fail to meet the London Objective of being a zero-carbon city by 2050, contrary to policies SI 2 (Minimising greenhouse gas emissions) of the London Plan (2021), policy&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;LP55 (Mitigating Climate Change)&amp;nbsp;of Hackneyâs Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to secure car-free housing, would be likely to promote the use of non-sustainable modes of transport and contribute to air pollution and congestion in the surrounding area, contrary to policies T6 (Car Parking) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP45 (Parking and Car Free Development) of Hackneyâs Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to secure a contribution towards affordable housing fails to deliver the maximum reasonable amount of affordable housing and is therefore contrary to policy H4 (Delivering affordable housing) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP13 (Affordable housing) of Hackneyâs Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
